CONDOLENCES: Expresses the condolences of the House of Representatives on the death
of Kathleen "Kay" Gibbons Favrot
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To express the condolences of the House of Representatives on the death of Kathleen "Kay"
3 Gibbons Favrot.
4 WHEREAS, it is with immense sadness and profound regret that the House of
5 Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana has learned of the passing, on December 13,
6 2025, of Kathleen "Kay" Gibbons Favrot; and
7 WHEREAS, Kathleen was born on July 17, 1936, in New Orleans, Louisiana, a city
8 she loved dearly; she graduated from the Academy of the Sacred Heart and attended
9 Maryville College of the Sacred Heart in St. Louis, Missouri; her education instilled in her
10 an enduring devotion to faith, service, and community; and
11 WHEREAS, Ms. Favrot was a woman of deep faith and boundless generosity; she
12 was devoted to the Academy of the Sacred Heart and served on the school's board and in
13 numerous volunteer roles; she was enthusiastic, selfless, and unwavering in her support of
14 the school and countless individuals and charitable organizations; and
15 WHEREAS, Ms. Favrot loved the Christmas season; she was an incredibly generous
16 gifter, and she relentlessly requested people's wish lists; she found immense joy in giving
17 to others and ensured that all of her loved ones felt remembered and celebrated; and
18 WHEREAS, Ms. Favrot was an expert grammarian and loved the English language;
19 her grandchildren can attest that no grammatical error could get past her keen eyes; and
20 WHEREAS, Kathleen "Kay" Gibbons Favrot is survived by her four children, James
21 Favrot (Sheila), Kathleen Favrot Van Horn (Charlie), Semmes Favrot (Catherine), and
